small bogs along trickles of sky between thesnowbank and the orchid. And yet--was that all? What form of mysteriouspursuit caused me to get my feet wet like a child, to pant up a talus, tostare <155> every dandelion in the face, to start at every colored motepassing just beyond my field of vision? What was the dream sensation ofhaving come empty-handed--without what? A gun? A wand? This I dared notprobe lest I wound the raw fell under my thin identity.

